      <item>
        <title>Chef Has a Different Gemrc</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;While the global &lt;code&gt;/etc/gemrc&lt;/code&gt; configuration is standard for system installed gems, gems
that come in omnibus packages like &lt;code&gt;chef-client&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;chefdk&lt;/code&gt;, etc don’t respect
this setting. It &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22259362/where-chef-store-the-gem-source-repository/28816880#28816880&quot;&gt;turns out&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;code&gt;chef-client&lt;/code&gt; it’s &lt;code&gt;/opt/chef/embedded/etc/gemrc&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Thu, 05 Nov 2015 22:42:47 -0500</pubDate>
